Package InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement.Exception.Creation

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IncorrectInputException
    Signals the use of a PlatformInput that does not correspond to the predefined input for a module.
    IncorrectIONameException
    Signals that, in configuring a module, an incorrect name for an input or output was declared.
    ModuleCreationException
    Signals an error while creating or configuring the instances of PlatformModule
    ModuleManagerException
    Signals an error in the ModuleManager operation.
    ModuleNotDefinedException
    Signals that a certain PlatformModule could not be found in the defined modules.
